$ Git: Credential Helper
@ credential helper

A *credential helper* is a program, independent from Git, from which Git can request credentials (i.e. a combination of username and → development/security/password).

There are two types of credential helpers:
table { ll
  Cache ☰ The credentials are stored for a certain amount of time in memory.
  Store ☰ The credentials are stored permanently, typically on a disk.
table }
